<img src="https://biz-file.com/c/1906/500480-625x325.jpg" alt="Image source: Gallo/Getty." width="625" height="325">Image source: Gallo/Getty.StarTimes Nigeria, CEO, David Zhang, said: “Plus TV Africa has done well during the pilot phase of the broadcast hence the upgrade to our dish platform. Right now, in all of Africa where we broadcast, Plus TV Africa can be enjoyed.”Also commenting, managing director and editor-in-chief at Plus TV Africa, Kayode Akintemi said: “The upgrade to broadcast across Pan-Africa is proof that the hard work the company has put into creating unique and engaging content for various category of audience has paid off.”Plus TV Africa is an Afropolitan 24 hour TV News Channel owned by General News & Entertainment Company (GNEC) Media Group. The station is set up to provide news content to cater to the African professional and the millennials who seek quality African news, stories and content.Source: NexTVAfrica.com.